HEADWORD: Turtleback
<hw>Tur"tle*back`</hw> <pr>(t⟦ucir⟧r"t'l-b⟦acr⟧k`)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Archaeol.)</fld> <def>A rude stone celt of a form
suggesting the back of a turtle.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Naut.)</fld> <def>A convex deck at the bow or stern
of a vessel, so made to shed the seas quickly.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Turtledove</ent>⟦br⟧
